                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3409: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-23T20:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 23, 1920—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>187. Referring to final question in our 180 of July 16, 2 p.m. and to your 191,
                    noon, July 21. Who made suggestion upon which Ministers acted and what form did
                    action take? We are waiting for report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
